<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[809,1421,570,798]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
Previously, two individuals were recorded by Wolton 
<emphasis box="[902,953,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
. (1982, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="E. Geoffroy" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[1083,1262,604,630]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="commersoni">
<emphasis box="[1083,1262,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">H. commersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<bibRefCitation author="DECHER, J. &amp; J. FAHR" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" pagination="5 - 30" refId="ref12281" refString="DECHER, J., and J. FAHR. 2007. A conservation assessment of bats (Chiroptera) of Draw River, Boi-Tano, and Krokosua Hills Forest Reserves in the Western Region of Ghana. Myotis, 43: 5 - 30." type="journal article" year="2007">Decher and Fahr (2007)</bibRefCitation>
mention specimens from Mt 
<collectingRegion box="[1341,1421,637,663]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Nimba</collectingRegion>
at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[978,1183,671,697]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.585" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.47" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="m" value="1585.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="1470.0">1,470 to 1,700 m</quantity>
. During this survey, it was recorded widely in forested and disturbed habitats in Liberian 
<collectingRegion box="[1051,1134,738,764]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Nimba</collectingRegion>
, ranging from 
<quantity box="[1313,1389,738,764]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="m" value="460.0">460 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[809,906,772,798]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="m" value="1060.0">1,060 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</paragraph>
